Sister Marilyn Clarke with the baby found in Missionvale. Picture supplied. Social workers at Dora Nginza Hospital are appealing to the public to assist in locating the family of a newborn baby who was found abandoned in Missionvale on Monday (20/03/17). The baby, who was found by a passerby in the bushes, is healthy and was clothed in a black and white jumper and wrapped in a maroon blanket. Anybody with information on the parents or family of the baby can contact social worker Pamela Rubushe on 041 4064328 or 041 4064114. Related Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share